## Basic of working with github ##
##################################

## First clone your remote repository to your home directory
git clone <https of your repository>

## Move to your local copy of your remote repository
cd <to your local copy of your remote rep>

## Check if your local repository is up-to-date with the remote
git check

## Make changes in your local repository as needed 

## Check if your local repository is up-to-date with the remote
git check
## Changes, new files, deleted files should be now listed

## Add desired changes that are going to be pushed to remote
git add <changes file(s)>

## Commit those changes and add informative message '-m' describing the change made
git commit -m "Added new file ..." 

## Push these changes to the remote repository
git push origin master
